@section Call Operator

The @code{metalua} state object can be called, with an argument of the index, to return a copyable value from the stack. This value is not modified or popped.

See also, @ref{Definitions, multilua.fetchable, multilua.fetchable}.

WARNING: If a value being passed cannot simply be copied, it will raise an error.

This can currently copy the current values:

@itemize
@item @code{nil}
@item @code{integer}
@item @code{number}
@item @code{boolean}
@item @code{string}
@item @code{table}
@item @code{CFunction}
@item @code{Lua function}
@item @code{lightuserdata}
@end itemize

WARNING: For Lua functions, tables, if the originating state is closed, and then they are attempted to be used, will result in Undefined Behaviour.

@cartouche
@verbatim
local multilua = require "multilua"

local obj = multilua.new()

obj[#obj + 1] = 10

assert(obj(-1) == 10)
@end verbatim
@end cartouche
